added.title: Skulls And Sillybones
added.description: Buster, Plucky, and Hamton join an exclusive secret society but soon realize that the perks promised aren't worth the sacrifices. Meanwhile, Babs and Sweetie start their own public society that becomes a big hit on campus.

added.title: Extra, So Extra
added.description: Babs realizes Acme Loo's school paper has closed so she starts a new one with her pal Sweetie. But when Plucky starts a gossipy tabloid to compete against them, which paper will come out on top?

added.title: Jelly Aches
added.description: The school descends into chaos after getting a visit from Gazunga, the Jealousy Troll.

added.title: The Gold and the Stickerful
added.description: Courtney becomes infatuated with a new gold sticker incentive program that Chef introduces to the class.

added.title: Exit 9B
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are the only ones who can save the park after everyone gets brain washed.

added.title: Starter Pack
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to stop Muscle Man from messing with Thomas.

added.title: Payback/Party Bus
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are driving to a Halloween party and tell scary stories to pass the time.

added.title: Wallpaper Man
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are driving to a Halloween party and tell scary stories to pass the time.

added.title: Pie Contest
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to prove to Benson that they can be judges at the pie contest.

added.title: Prankless
added.description: The guys want to win a prank war with a rival park.

added.title: Death Bear
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to get a picture in death bear's cage to impress Margaret and Eileen.

added.title: Fuzzy Dice
added.description: Everyone wants to give Pops some fuzzy dice for his birthday.

added.title: Sugar Rush
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to pick up the donuts for the morning meeting.

added.title: Bad Kiss
added.description: Mordecai finally makes his move and tries to kiss Margaret.

added.title: The Great Veggie War
added.description: The bears return to the Veggie Kingdom to visit their old friend Lima, only to find the kingdom at war with a familiar yet unexpected foe. Can the bears help save the veggie kingdom from total annihilation?

added.title: Trade-Off!
added.description: Darkstar, convinces Kevin to join him in a quest for an ancient artifact with the ability to help them both escape their current degenerate states.

added.title: Busy Box
added.description: Kevin, Ben, and Gwen find a curious box that has the ability to turn into a robot version of whatever it sees. All is well till the Vreedles show up.

added.title: Con of Rath
added.description: Ben is on a special mission when the Omnitrix malfunctions and turns him into an Appoplexian named Rath who wants to fight anything that breaths.

added.title: Primus
added.description: In the middle of fighting a Techadon robot, Ben, Kevin, and Gwen are unexpectedly transported by the Omnitrix to an alien planet named Primus.

added.title: Time Heals
added.description: Gwen travels back in time to prevent the accident that turned Kevin into a monster from ever happening. But she ends up altering history forever.

added.title: The Legend of Jack O'Lantern/The Mecha T-Rex
added.description: It's Halloween and everything is set for the Zee Mobile to pull the haunted hayride… until it drives away./Timmy can't wait to trick or treat as a Mecha T-Rex, but his Halloween is almost ruined when he can't reach the arms to his costume.

added.title: If It's Broke, Fix It
added.description: Dibble helps Grumpy work on his latest invention, a device to stop Bluster's bad vibe plow. Dibble's endless high spirits and sense of fun wear on Grumpy, until he finally says she can't work with him anymore. It's only later that Grumpy understands he needs Dibble's free-spirit inventiveness and creative energy.

added.title: One More Game
added.description: When David wants to play video games all day, Barney puts a magical spin on some physical play that brings all the kids together in a game. David realizes the value of balancing both kinds of fun.

added.title: Monster Truck Amok
added.description: Grundy, a giant monster truck, causes chaos as he stomps around Gotham and creates a mess. He's too powerful for the Batwheels to stop, but Buff finds a friendly solution to end the city shaking shenanigans.

added.title: MOE Alone
added.description: A sneaky trick strands the Batwheels at the docks, clearing the way for a Batcave heist by the Legion of Zoom. It's up to MOE to stop the Zoomers with zany improvised tricks and traps with a little help from Ace and Batcomputer.

added.title: When You're A Jet
added.description: Green Arrow and his Arrowplane, Goldie, come to help Batman take on the Riddler. Batwing is so happy to have another flying vehicle around that she brings Goldie to life and the two become BFFs. But when Goldie eventually has to leave, Batwing learns that saying goodbye doesn't always mean forever!

added.title: The Whatsacallit of Treetop Woods/Nat in the Dark!
added.description: Berta is opening an exhibit on the Whatsacallit of Treetop Woods. If only she could get a picture to prove it's real./Gerry and Nat are leading the Treetop Troops on a hike, but Nat finds himself lost in the woods as it gets darker.

added.title: All Mechas on Deck/Where There's A Wheel, There's A Way
added.description: Lloyd's testing a wind-up powered go-cart, but a problem arises when it keeps running out of energy./Sif's coming in for a landing at the rocket launch site - until her rocket is pushed off course by a satellite!

added.title: Waffle Cones for Whiffles
added.description: The Whiffles are too hot and tired to work because their daily treat, colorful ice in Waffles Cones delivered by the whimsical "Icelings," hasn't arrived - the Icelings have mysteriously disappeared. As the Care Bears search for them, Share volunteers to make the treats. It's much more than she can handle but she's determined to go-it-alone and not ask for help. Things get out of hand and Share ends up snared in Bluster's trap with the Icelings, who help her to realize that we get more done when we work together.

added.title: Monsterplant
added.description: Bluster creates a mad scientist's monster from a clump of moss and sends it to scare the Whiffles away. The kindhearted Monsterplant just wants to be friends with them, but the Whiffles are frightened away by how he looks. Share and Dibble work together to show the Whiffles how nice Monsterplant is on the inside.
